This is one of the first SCPs I ever read (I still have nightmares).

Anyway, this SCP has a very strange and confusing vibe to it (but that's a good thing). It is especially an oddity in this sea of SCPs in which we voyage through.

My explanation of SCP-957 goes as follows: This  is an extra terrestrial/interdimensional being which has, along with several others of its kind, arrived at our planet to research human gullibility. They study this attribute by convincing the human subject that the two are related, and observing what lengths the human will go to for the being masquerading as the human's family member.

But hey, that's just a theory. An SCP theory!








-Crunchy






